long_desc.thetext:
I would prefere to implement a new qx.io.request.Image class which allows the same behavior like other io.request classes with more ability to add and remove listeners for events like : "loaded", "failed", "aborted". This class can be combined with the currently available ImageLoader class. The ImageLoader can be the part who manages all image sources.


// initialize new resource
var img = new qx.io.request.Image("/some/path/image.png");
// add some listeners
img.addListener("loaded", somefunction, this);
// load image
req.load();
